            . I live in <placeName id="t18120916-113-crimeloc631">Bath-street, City-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18120916-113-crimeloc631" type="placeName" value="Bath-street, City-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18120916-113-crimeloc631" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18120916-113-off629 t18120916-113-crimeloc631"></join>. I am a <rs id="t18120916-113-viclabel632" type="occupation">shoemaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18120916-113-victim954 t18120916-113-viclabel632"></join>. I lost the boots on Thursday, the 10th of this month. I was at work in the shop until half past eight. I went into the back parlour to have my supper, and about nine I heard a noise at the shop window. I immediately pursued it. He ran off. I took him, and brought him in doors. One of my children found the boots at the door. These are boots. They are mine.</p>
               <p>Q. What had he done with the boots - A. He flung them away, because I pursued him close. They were picked up by the children, and given to me. I am sure the prisoner is the man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18120916-113-person956">
                  JAMES 
                  GEARY
               <interp inst="t18120916-113-person956" type="surname" value="GEARY"></interp>
